<Content>For a romantic weekend, THIS IS THE HOTEL FOR YOU! If you are planning on proposing or wanting a romantic weekend away this is the place for you! I truly reccommend the Starlight Lounge on the 21st floor. with the ambiance, exceptional quality and friendly staff and amazing view! Just simply amazing to look out on SF and see the clouds role in while the jazz music plays! One of those breathtaking moments! ~ScottFirst off it was the hotel reservation staff that made every single bit of difference. I tried to book online and waited too long only to find the price point I wanted was sold out. I called in desperation and explained that I was proposing to my girlfriend in SF that weekend and pleaded that I was on a tight budget. I would rather not start a lifelong marriage with debt in these current times. The reservation operator was %110 understanding and did everything to find a room cheaper even than I had originally seen on the web!!!!!I was so excited that I actually decided right then and there on the phone that it was a sign that I was going to go through with it and propose! I don't think he truly understood what he had done for us! So, when we arrived I proposed in the Starlight Lounge, she said yes!!!!!! THANK YOU THANK YOU THANK YOU! We will be back in one year, five years, and forever together to renew our vows, no matter the cost we will come back! You have made not only customers, but friends for life! All the best wishes to you and your staff!Door greeter was excellent!The grand entrance when you walk in and warm smiles made us realize we came to the right place. Great atmosphere for a romantic weekend. So much more personal/personable than a brand name hotel like the Westin. We love the more cosy quaint atmosphere than you get at a big expensive hotel. Not that there is anything wrong with them at all. It is just like we felt we arrived in Dublin, rather than London metro feeling.The watchful caring staff were always attentive, we never worried 